  ‚ä¢= text ‚Üê "## Cell v0.1 Spec ‚Äî Key Constraints

Cells declare inputs with `given` and outputs with `yield`.
All inputs must be fully bound before evaluation.
There is no conditional `given` ‚Äî every declared input is required.
There is no branching construct ‚Äî cells execute linearly by data dependency.
There is no `try/fallback` pattern ‚Äî oracle failure (‚ä®?) is the only recovery.
There is no way to express 'evaluate A, then choose B or C based on result.'
There is no guard clause on cells ‚Äî a cell cannot say 'only run me if X.'
Versioning of evolved cells uses prime marks: cell, cell', cell''.

Open Questions from v0.1:
1. Error handling ‚Äî what when ‚ä¢= throws or ‚à¥ produces wrong type?
2. Versioning beyond prime marks ‚Äî ¬ßcell''' doesn't scale.
3. Streaming ‚Äî need ~ annotation for incremental input.
4. Oracle distinction ‚Äî assert vs rule, soft vs hard preconditions."

  yield text ‚â° "(Cell v0.1 key constraints excerpt ‚Äî 15 lines covering conditional, branching, and versioning gaps)"

