  -- LLM evaluates. Tentative output:

  yield proposed-syntax ‚â° "## Proposed: Guard Clause with `where`

### New construct: guarded cell declaration

‚ä¢ cell-name | condition
  given ...
  yield ...

The `|` (pipe/guard) after the cell name specifies a boolean precondition.
The cell is only evaluated when the guard is true. If false, the cell
produces ‚ä• (bottom) for all yields ‚Äî dependents see it as 'not available.'

### Syntax

‚ä¢ name | guard-expression
  given input1
  yield output1
  ...

Guard expressions can reference any bound cell output:
  | classify‚Üílabel = 'toxic'
  | score‚Üívalue ‚â• 0.5
  | config‚Üímode ‚àà {'fast', 'accurate'}

### Variant cells (sugar for common dispatch pattern)

‚ä¢ handle | classify‚Üílabel
  | 'toxic':
    ‚à¥ Rewrite text to remove toxicity...
  | 'borderline':
    ‚à¥ Flag for human review...
  | 'clean':
    ‚à¥ Pass through unchanged...

This desugars to three guarded cells: handle:toxic, handle:borderline, handle:clean.
Only the matching variant evaluates. Others produce ‚ä•.

### Bottom propagation

When a guarded cell produces ‚ä•:
- Cells depending on its output are SKIPPED (not blocked forever)
- ‚ä• propagates through the dependency graph
- A cell receiving ‚ä• for ANY input also produces ‚ä•
- The `merge` pattern becomes unnecessary ‚Äî only the active branch produces values

### New symbol

| Symbol | Name | Meaning |
|--------|------|---------|
| `\\|` | guard | conditional cell activation |
| `‚ä•` | bottom | cell did not fire (guard false) |"

  yield rationale ‚â° "Guard clauses address all 4 root causes:
1. CONDITIONAL ACTIVATION: `| condition` replaces the N/A hack. Cells don't evaluate when irrelevant.
2. DISPATCH: Variant cells (`| value: ...`) replace manual routing with pattern matching.
3. PATTERN MATCHING: The `|` syntax IS pattern matching at the cell level.
4. CONTROL FLOW: Guards separate routing from oracles. Oracles verify correctness. Guards select execution path.

Design choice: `|` (pipe/guard) was chosen over alternatives because:
- `given x where cond` ‚Äî conflates input declaration with routing
- `‚ä¢‚ä∏ route(...)` ‚Äî introduces a new cell-type sigil (heavier syntax)
- `given? x if cond` ‚Äî optional inputs are a different feature (partial evaluation)
The `|` guard is orthogonal to `given`, `yield`, `‚ä®`, and `‚ä¢‚àò`. It composes cleanly."

  yield compatibility-analysis ‚â° "Backward compatible. No existing v0.1 program uses `|` after cell names.
The `‚ä•` value is new but only appears when guards are used. Existing programs
without guards behave identically. The variant cell syntax is pure sugar ‚Äî
it desugars to multiple standard cells with guards."

